Popular Nollywood actor, Dammy Eke is dead. According to multiple reports, the screen star reportedly slumped and died at a bar in Rivers State on April 28, 2019. It is gathered that his brother has since confirmed the news of his death although the cause of death is yet to be determined as at the time of filing this report. The deceased was a Justice of Peace, JP, an Ambassador for Peace of UPA, and an actor. He featured in various Nollywood films such as Reincarnated God of War, Pains of Sister Rose, Mysterious Events’ and a host of others. His untimely demise is coming five years after losing his father, Frank Eke. The late senior Eke was the first civilian governor of Rivers State and he died at 83.